    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-12T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="316"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Norway/16a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-12T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 12, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. No reply received to instruction No. 300, July 5, 1935. Telegraph action
                    taken. Endeavor expedite reply and inform Norwegian Government also that
                    Norwegian steamer <hi rend="italic">Trajan</hi> unloaded nearly 15,000 cases
                    alcohol on high seas into four or five smuggling vessels in August, and that
                    Norwegian steamer <hi rend="italic">Reidun</hi> is at present unloading nearly
                    20,000 cases alcohol on high seas into smuggling vessels. Several United States
                    Coast Guard vessels are standing by, observing procedure.</p>
                <pb facs="0539" n="437" xml:id="pg_437"/>
                <p>Suggest action of Norwegian vessels appears to be contrary to Norwegian law
                    regarding participation in smuggling directed against foreign country.</p>
                <p>Details of unloading contained in instruction No. 13, November 4, 1935.<note
                        n="71" xml:id="d316fn71">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
